## Why they compound instead of just adding

- **Model-only** fixes the *per-token rate* and kills the hidden "thinking" overhead (gemini-3.5-flash burns ~600-2,300 invisible tokens per call that the lite tier simply doesn't spend) — this alone gets ~94% of the win.
- **Code-only** fixes the *call count* (1 request instead of 11) but each of those calls still pays gemini-3.5-flash's expensive per-token rate and thinking tax.
- **Both together**: fewer calls *and* each call is ~26x cheaper per token — that's why it's not 94%+81% (impossible), it's multiplicative: ~15.5x × ~6.7x ≈ ~104x.

So: **model-only already gets you 93.6% of the savings**, but stacking the code fix on top takes you from "15x cheaper" to "104x cheaper" for the same clicked action. Your instinct is confirmed — flash-lite is the move, and doing both is clearly worth it.

